This study is part of a large clinical trial examining the effect of fluticasone propionate in the treatment of the common cold. 11 Two hundred patients participated in the treatment study; 40 of these patients were randomized Objective. The purpose of this investigation was to study the effect of a potent topical steroid, fluticasone propionate, on patients with early signs and symptoms of the common cold. To characterize the mucosal inflammatory response, salivary defense factors and flow rate in these patients were analyzed. 


